<paragraph id="EAC65F7B8ADF61B0D5F2F3D0BF1828AB" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
3.2.9. 
<taxonomicName id="520D1BEFBCDFDB40EFFA499D441CDA62" LSID="C59CC418-9692-54E4-A9E8-760C8C4A1EE9" authority="Bey-Bienko, 1950" authorityName="Bey-Bienko" authorityYear="1950" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Episymploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Episymploce" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Episymploce Bey-Bienko, 1950</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3B0E49C2DB6D72C6835F77E256EBC507" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="notes">
<paragraph id="AC8633E166A60A55322A44FA799C1644" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6255F3C9EB5D7C2F174EB7BD2D59A655" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
In our phylogenetic analysis (the type species 
<taxonomicName id="56FD17D2444DA16D6CA6534562740A57" authorityName="Bei-Bienko" authorityYear="1950" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Episymploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Episymploce paradoxura" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paradoxura">
<emphasis id="3D8D39CB99F42FCC632D103D929F1504" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Episymploce paradoxura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bey-Bienko, 1950 not included), 
<taxonomicName id="47972E965C963A0F0082CA24E9EB1326" authorityName="Jin &amp; Zhao &amp; Han &amp; Li &amp; Wang &amp; Che" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Jin &amp; Zhao &amp; Han &amp; Li &amp; Wang &amp; Che" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Symploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Symploce torchaceus" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torchaceus">
<emphasis id="79DBA1BDA202F34DA0A0B80F5964819D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Symploce torchaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Feng and Woo, 1999 and 
<taxonomicName id="8F5E9D3CFF756FBB104286C67E325ED2" authorityName="Jin &amp; Zhao &amp; Han &amp; Li &amp; Wang &amp; Che" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Jin &amp; Zhao &amp; Han &amp; Li &amp; Wang &amp; Che" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Symploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Symploce wulingensis" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wulingensis">
<emphasis id="28860F648587383DB4C17C4C0398AC52" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Symploce wulingensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Feng and Woo, 1993 were recovered as sister taxa and deeply embedded within the clade of 
<taxonomicName id="8C0AD562A57BDCA3531B62DC9CC3982F" authorityName="Bey-Bienko" authorityYear="1950" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Episymploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Episymploce" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C83B3A22D956586AA6888FAD5BCBAD0A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Episymploce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 2 new combinations were set up accordingly, and 1 synonymy was proposed as follows.
</paragraph>
